---
import Layout from '~/layouts/Layout.astro'
import { createWebPageSchema } from '~/utils/schema'

const pageSchema = createWebPageSchema({
  name: 'LAOM Manifesto',
  url: Astro.url.toString(),
  description:
    'Living and creating differently: a manifesto for regenerative living and work rooted in freedom, collaboration, and the living world.',
})
---

<Layout
  title="Manifesto â€“ LAOM"
  description="Living and creating differently: a manifesto for regenerative living and work rooted in freedom, collaboration, and the living world."
  seo={{ ldJSON: pageSchema }}
>
  <section class="py-32 lg:py-40 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-10 sm:px-16 lg:px-24 text-center">
      <span class="block text-xs font-light tracking-[0.2em] uppercase text-black/40 mb-6">LAOM MANIFESTO</span>
      <h1 class="text-5xl md:text-6xl lg:text-7xl font-light text-black mb-6 tracking-tight">
        Living and creating differently
      </h1>
      <p class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-light text-black/60 leading-relaxed">
        We live in a time marked by crises of connection. LAOM aims to respond to this necessary transformation by
        creating a living, flexible, and autonomous ecosystem.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-24 bg-[#faf9f6]">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-10 sm:px-16 lg:px-24">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-light text-black mb-8">Crises of connection</h2>
      <div class="space-y-4 text-lg font-light text-black/70 leading-relaxed">
        <p>Connection to self: a fast-paced way of life that fragments our identities and distances us from our deeper aspirations.</p>
        <p>Connection to others: a hyper-connected world where isolation and individualism are on the rise.</p>
        <p>
          Connection to nature: an economic model that exploits without restoring, putting at risk the ecosystems we
          depend on.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="mt-10 space-y-6 text-lg font-light text-black/70 leading-relaxed">
        <p>
          Faced with these challenges, we need new forms of living and working that regenerate our relationships, our
          environments, and the way we create value.
        </p>
        <p>
          LAOM is designed as a space where the liquid economy and the regenerative economy meet, enabling each person
          to evolve freely while leaving a positive footprint on their environment.
        </p>
        <p>
          This manifesto lays the foundations of a clear commitment: to design spaces that nourish people and their
          environment, where innovation and sustainability are not compromises but fundamental pillars.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-24 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-10 sm:px-16 lg:px-24">
      <div class="space-y-10">
        <div class="border border-black/10 bg-white p-8 lg:p-10 shadow-sm">
          <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-light text-black mb-4">1. Awareness and intention</h2>
          <p class="text-lg font-light text-black/70 leading-relaxed">
            We believe the future of living and working rests on the balance between freedom, collaboration, and
            regeneration. LAOM is a space where the liquid economy and the regenerative economy meet, enabling each
            person to evolve freely while leaving a positive footprint on their environment.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-6 text-lg font-light text-black/70 leading-relaxed">
            Our intention is to create a living ecosystem where individuals find meaning, inspiration, and
            opportunities to build a future aligned with their deepest values.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="border border-black/10 bg-white p-8 lg:p-10 shadow-sm">
          <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-light text-black mb-4">2. Connection to self</h2>
          <ul class="space-y-3 text-lg font-light text-black/70 leading-relaxed">
            <li>Explore and deepen your own life path.</li>
            <li>Develop personal and professional autonomy in a framework that nurtures creativity.</li>
            <li>Align your work and projects with your values and deeper aspirations.</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-6 text-lg font-light text-black/70 leading-relaxed">
            We value personal flourishing by integrating practices that nourish the mind, body, and life mission of
            each individual.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="border border-black/10 bg-white p-8 lg:p-10 shadow-sm">
          <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-light text-black mb-4">3. Connection to others</h2>
          <p class="text-lg font-light text-black/70 leading-relaxed">
            We believe in a fluid and caring community, where exchanges are based on sharing, co-creation, and the
            transmission of knowledge.
          </p>
          <ul class="mt-6 space-y-3 text-lg font-light text-black/70 leading-relaxed">
            <li>Cultivate sincere and constructive human relationships.</li>
            <li>Foster synergies between entrepreneurs, artists, and innovators.</li>
            <li>Offer a living and working framework that stimulates spontaneous collaboration and collective intelligence.</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-6 text-lg font-light text-black/70 leading-relaxed">
            We create spaces and practices that facilitate listening, cooperation, and mutual support to build a
            dynamic and inspiring community.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="border border-black/10 bg-white p-8 lg:p-10 shadow-sm">
          <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-light text-black mb-4">4. Connection to nature and the world</h2>
          <p class="text-lg font-light text-black/70 leading-relaxed">
            We fully integrate ecological regeneration into the way LAOM operates.
          </p>
          <ul class="mt-6 space-y-3 text-lg font-light text-black/70 leading-relaxed">
            <li>Energy and food autonomy: produce more than we consume.</li>
            <li>Bio-inspired design: rely on living systems principles to build resilient infrastructures.</li>
            <li>Reduce carbon footprint through durable materials, circular economy, and respectful practices.</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-6 text-lg font-light text-black/70 leading-relaxed">
            We make LAOM a laboratory for experimentation to reconcile technological progress with respect for the
            living world, integrating ancestral know-how and contemporary innovations.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="border border-black/10 bg-white p-8 lg:p-10 shadow-sm">
          <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-light text-black mb-4">5. Regenerative and liquid economic model</h2>
          <p class="text-lg font-light text-black/70 leading-relaxed">
            LAOM does not follow a fixed model, but evolves with the needs of those who bring it to life.
          </p>
          <ul class="mt-6 space-y-3 text-lg font-light text-black/70 leading-relaxed">
            <li>Enable total flexibility through a hybrid model combining temporary residence, coworking, and collaborative space.</li>
            <li>Support a circular and regenerative economy where every contribution enriches the ecosystem.</li>
            <li>Encourage experimentation and rapid iteration within a supportive and inspiring environment.</li>
            <li>Support on-site agricultural practices.</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-6 text-lg font-light text-black/70 leading-relaxed">
            We believe in an economic model based on exchange, resilience, and the creation of shared value.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
